WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:04.004
♪ ♪

00:06.923 --> 00:09.467
♪ <i>Shadows are falling </i>♪

00:09.551 --> 00:11.678
♪ <i>And I'm running out of breath </i>♪

00:11.761 --> 00:15.181
♪ <i>Keep me in your heart for a while </i>♪

00:15.265 --> 00:16.850
♪ ♪

00:16.933 --> 00:20.395
♪ <i>If I leave you, it doesn't mean </i>♪

00:20.478 --> 00:23.064
♪ <i>I love you any less </i>♪

00:23.148 --> 00:26.317
♪ <i>Keep me in your heart for a while </i>♪

00:26.401 --> 00:27.819
(crying)

00:27.902 --> 00:30.864
♪ <i>When you get up in the morning </i>♪

00:30.947 --> 00:33.742
♪ <i>And you see that crazy sun </i>♪

00:33.825 --> 00:35.035
♪ <i>Keep me in... </i>♪

00:35.118 --> 00:36.995
No. I still haven't heard anything.

00:37.078 --> 00:38.830
(sighs)
I'm really trying not to freak out, Tobe.

00:38.913 --> 00:40.915
♪ <i>There's a train leaving... </i>♪

00:40.999 --> 00:42.292
Wait, someone's at the door.

00:45.086 --> 00:46.338
No, it's just Kevin and Madison.

00:46.421 --> 00:48.381
Oh, well, hello to you, too.

00:48.465 --> 00:50.467
Um, will you just keep looking?

00:50.550 --> 00:52.302
Just... I'll call you if I hear anything.

00:52.385 --> 00:53.720
Okay.

00:53.803 --> 00:55.889
-What's up?
-(sighs) Oh, God.

00:55.972 --> 00:58.683
Mom went to get a birthday cake,
and she hasn't come back.

00:58.767 --> 01:00.518
I tried calling her.
She's not answering.

01:00.602 --> 01:02.520
So, Toby went to the bakery,

01:02.604 --> 01:04.356
and apparently,
she didn't even make it there.

01:04.439 --> 01:06.566
-Oh, my God.
-Okay. I-I'm-I'm gonna go...

01:06.649 --> 01:08.193
I'm gonna go look for her.
I'm gonna go help.

01:08.276 --> 01:09.944
-Uh, are you okay?
-Yeah.

01:10.028 --> 01:11.071
-No, yeah, go.
-You sure?

01:11.154 --> 01:12.238
Wait, what's going on?

01:12.322 --> 01:14.616
Uh, no, nothing.
I had a little morning sickness,

01:14.699 --> 01:16.993
-but...
-MIGUEL: Oh, thank God. Um...

01:17.077 --> 01:18.161
Yes.

01:18.244 --> 01:20.288
Yes. Of course.

01:20.372 --> 01:21.998
Um, thank you very much.

01:22.082 --> 01:23.625
Yeah, we're here.

01:23.708 --> 01:25.543
Okay.

01:27.587 --> 01:29.381
S-So, the cops have her.

01:29.464 --> 01:32.592
She, uh... She had an episode.

01:32.676 --> 01:35.387
They're bringing her back here.

01:36.846 --> 01:38.598
Let's all just, um...

01:38.682 --> 01:40.016
Let's just stay calm.

01:40.100 --> 01:41.810
We don't know what kind of state
she's gonna be in,

01:41.893 --> 01:43.436
and-and I don't want to panic her.

01:47.315 --> 01:48.608
<i>(car door closes)</i>

01:48.692 --> 01:50.193
OFFICER:
All right, ma'am, you're home.

01:50.276 --> 01:51.945
Everything's gonna be okay.

01:54.739 --> 01:55.949
Mom, come on in.

01:56.032 --> 01:57.575
-Hi.
-Hi.

01:57.659 --> 01:59.619
Thank you very much for bringing her home.

01:59.703 --> 02:01.955
♪ ♪

02:06.001 --> 02:08.712
Okay, thanks.
Oh, how's she doing back there?

02:08.795 --> 02:10.130
Uh, she's laying down.

02:10.213 --> 02:12.048
She's a little nauseous.

02:12.132 --> 02:13.466
My fiancée's got morning sickness

02:13.550 --> 02:14.843
at all hours of the day.

02:14.926 --> 02:17.012
OFFICER:
Oh. Try ginger tea.

02:17.095 --> 02:18.346
It worked for me...

02:18.430 --> 02:20.265
♪ ♪

02:23.184 --> 02:25.478
-Hey.
-Madison okay?

02:25.562 --> 02:26.938
Yeah. Yeah, she's okay.

02:27.022 --> 02:29.065
-Did you hear anything from Mom's doctor?
-No.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.109
Miguel left her a message.

02:33.194 --> 02:35.071
Kev, she was...

02:35.155 --> 02:37.032
she was gone.

02:37.115 --> 02:40.910
Like, like, her face was not her face.

02:40.994 --> 02:42.412
I know.

02:42.495 --> 02:45.248
It's too soon.
I'm not ready for this.

02:46.291 --> 02:48.001
Yeah, me neither.

02:50.420 --> 02:52.297
Obviously, at some point,

02:52.380 --> 02:54.841
you're gonna need to explain
your use of the word "fiancée."

02:54.924 --> 02:57.177
Yeah, it's a long story.

02:57.260 --> 02:58.303
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

02:58.386 --> 03:00.013
Well, it's a long car ride home.

03:00.096 --> 03:02.265
True that. Yeah.

03:05.310 --> 03:08.480
Okay, so, Kev, I tried calling you

03:08.563 --> 03:10.732
for, like, two hours,
and you weren't answering.

03:10.815 --> 03:13.109
-I'm sorry.
-(knock on door)

03:19.282 --> 03:20.283
(door opens)

03:33.922 --> 03:36.049
I-I didn't...
I didn't know you were, uh...

03:36.132 --> 03:37.676
Yeah.

03:37.759 --> 03:39.386
-Hey.
-Hey.

03:44.641 --> 03:45.684
Hi.

03:47.352 --> 03:50.146
I was just gonna call you about Mom.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.815
The cops found her.
They brought her home,

03:51.898 --> 03:53.233
so she's-she's here.

03:53.316 --> 03:56.236
She's safe.
She's-she's resting, so...

04:01.116 --> 04:03.159
Well, I wish I could
give you a massive hug,

04:03.243 --> 04:05.370
-but I don't know when you were...
-Um, I'm good.

04:05.453 --> 04:07.622
I get COVID tested
three times a week at city hall.

04:07.706 --> 04:10.375
Plus Beth's turned into Fauci
at home, so...

04:13.628 --> 04:14.754
You guys?

04:14.838 --> 04:17.132
Yeah, we're g...
We, um, we quarantined

04:17.215 --> 04:20.218
-for 20 days before we got here, so we're all good.
-(scoffs)

04:20.301 --> 04:21.886
Okay.

04:21.970 --> 04:23.555
I want to see her.

04:23.638 --> 04:25.515
-She upstairs? -KATE: Yeah.
-KEVIN: Yeah.

04:25.598 --> 04:27.559
Randall.

04:30.478 --> 04:32.981
There's no way we could've known
this was gonna happen.

04:33.064 --> 04:35.692
She was great before this.
You can ask Kate.

04:35.775 --> 04:38.111
I'm not questioning you, Kev.
I believe you.

04:38.194 --> 04:40.488
She's home, and that's what matters.

04:40.572 --> 04:42.157
It's cool.

04:44.075 --> 04:46.119
Cool.

04:46.202 --> 04:48.204
Oh, hey...

04:49.330 --> 04:51.166
Thank you for coming.

04:51.249 --> 04:53.293
I know the last thing
that you need right now is

04:53.376 --> 04:55.462
a terrified, panicked text
from your sister.

05:08.099 --> 05:09.642
<i>WOMAN:</i>
<i>Get it out.</i>

05:09.726 --> 05:12.062
-(pained gasps)
-(William speaks softly)

05:16.232 --> 05:19.486
(baby crying)

05:28.995 --> 05:31.623
♪ ♪

05:44.302 --> 05:46.012
Randall.

05:46.096 --> 05:47.847
-What...
-Hey.

05:47.931 --> 05:49.099
Sweetheart, I thought--

05:49.182 --> 05:51.226
I thought you weren't gonna make it.

05:51.309 --> 05:53.395
What, you think I'd miss our birthday?

05:53.478 --> 05:56.022
REBECCA:
Oh...

05:56.106 --> 05:58.400
(sighs)

05:58.483 --> 05:59.401
You know.

05:59.484 --> 06:02.362
-Kate called me.
-Mm.

06:04.781 --> 06:07.242
Are Beth and the girls with you?

06:07.325 --> 06:09.202
No, they're back home.

06:09.285 --> 06:11.162
-Next time.
-(sighs)

06:11.246 --> 06:14.207
I'm clear.
Kev said you are, too.

06:14.290 --> 06:15.750
I just want to be vigilant.

06:15.834 --> 06:17.127
-Just...
-Oh.

06:20.755 --> 06:22.757
(inhales, exhales deeply)

06:24.592 --> 06:26.678
You want to tell me what happened?

06:28.680 --> 06:31.099
Mm...

06:31.182 --> 06:33.226
I, uh...

06:33.309 --> 06:37.105
I d-- I don't even know what to say.

06:37.188 --> 06:40.567
Um, I went into town...

06:42.819 --> 06:45.989
...and then the next thing I knew...

06:46.072 --> 06:48.992
(sighs)
William was there.

06:50.744 --> 06:53.371
I mean, obviously not William, but I--

06:53.455 --> 06:56.249
Oh, God, I could have sworn it was him.

07:01.296 --> 07:04.632
I've been thinking about him a lot lately.

07:07.052 --> 07:10.013
Ever since we had our
conversation about the trial,

07:10.096 --> 07:13.850
and about me, um...
keeping him from you.

07:13.933 --> 07:16.936
We don't have to talk about that
right now, Mom. That's...

07:19.439 --> 07:22.067
Well, then, when?

07:24.235 --> 07:25.695
Hmm?

07:28.406 --> 07:30.992
Wh-What's going on there?

07:31.076 --> 07:34.162
Oh, that's just some poison ivy.

07:34.245 --> 07:35.622
Miguel and I have been gardening.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.290
I already took something for it.

07:40.919 --> 07:43.713
Do you think this would have
happened in St. Louis?

07:43.797 --> 07:46.383
I don't know.

07:48.760 --> 07:51.846
-I'm sorry I pushed that on you.
-No.

07:51.930 --> 07:53.306
No, no, no, sweetheart.

07:53.390 --> 07:56.267
You have nothing to apologize for.

08:01.356 --> 08:03.942
Are Beth and the girls with you?

08:07.445 --> 08:09.614
No, Mom.

08:09.698 --> 08:11.700
-Uh, next time.
-Okay.

08:12.701 --> 08:14.619
(sighs)

08:18.748 --> 08:20.917
♪ ♪

08:23.336 --> 08:26.840
Hey, excuse me, excuse me, um...

08:26.923 --> 08:28.425
My wife is Rebecca Pearson. I...

08:28.508 --> 08:30.802
I don't have an update yet, sir.

08:30.885 --> 08:33.596
Okay, wait, I-I don't--
I don't know what to do.

08:33.680 --> 08:37.225
Um, what can I do?

08:37.308 --> 08:39.561
You could pray.

08:48.153 --> 08:49.988
(gasps) Ha!

08:50.071 --> 08:52.657
-What are you doing?
-Kevin, you need to talk to Randall.

08:55.368 --> 08:58.246
Kev, I have tried my best
to stay out of this,

08:58.329 --> 09:01.041
but now Randall's acting
all weird with me, too.

09:01.124 --> 09:03.168
We haven't even done our birthday chant,

09:03.251 --> 09:04.210
and that's like canon.

09:04.294 --> 09:06.296
-Oh, Kate, Kate...
-No, Kevin.

09:06.379 --> 09:08.923
The world is on fire.

09:09.007 --> 09:11.593
This is enough. Fix it.

09:16.264 --> 09:18.767
♪ ♪

09:18.850 --> 09:20.769
(sighs)

09:41.289 --> 09:43.333
(door squeaks open)

09:44.834 --> 09:46.002
Hey.

09:46.086 --> 09:49.005
You know, after seeing
all those Internet videos

09:49.089 --> 09:51.591
of random objects that are actually cakes,

09:51.675 --> 09:54.511
it's kind of a letdown
to have a cake that just...

09:54.594 --> 09:55.970
looks like a cake.

10:00.308 --> 10:03.937
You know... (sighs)

10:04.020 --> 10:05.605
...when Rebecca and I first got here,

10:05.689 --> 10:07.107
we thought we were gonna
be here for a week.

10:07.190 --> 10:09.275
Two, max.

10:09.359 --> 10:12.153
Then that turned into a month.

10:12.237 --> 10:13.947
Then two months.

10:14.030 --> 10:16.616
But...

10:16.700 --> 10:18.702
she just kept feeling better.

10:20.620 --> 10:23.081
And I... I'm not an idiot
or anything like that.

10:23.164 --> 10:25.458
I know that there's-there's
no secret magic

10:25.542 --> 10:27.585
in the air that's gonna cure this,

10:27.669 --> 10:29.754
but... she just seemed like Rebecca again.

10:29.838 --> 10:31.381
You know?

10:33.174 --> 10:35.010
And now, with this....

10:35.093 --> 10:37.637
Oh, man.
It's just gonna take the legs

10:37.721 --> 10:39.889
right out from underneath her.

10:45.395 --> 10:48.273
Okay, I'm gonna
try to say something meaningful

10:48.356 --> 10:50.567
right now, Migs, and I got to warn you,

10:50.650 --> 10:54.571
it is gonna be a reach.
So, you just bear with me, okay?

10:54.654 --> 10:56.448
Okay.

10:56.531 --> 10:58.158
(clears throat)

11:00.660 --> 11:05.707
So every morning,
I take 20 milligrams of an antidepressant.

11:05.790 --> 11:09.085
Uh, I'm not sure who else
knows that besides Kate,

11:09.169 --> 11:11.671
but it's-it's not a big deal.

11:11.755 --> 11:16.760
So, about a month after
I started taking, uh, the meds,

11:16.843 --> 11:19.888
I called my doctor
to renew my prescription.

11:19.971 --> 11:21.723
And he said,
"Oh, no, don't worry about it.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.725
You have automatic refills."

11:25.518 --> 11:28.813
That hit me... really hard.

11:28.897 --> 11:32.150
You know, it just
made it feel so indefinite,

11:32.233 --> 11:34.361
so... so permanent.

11:34.444 --> 11:37.781
I said, "Is there ever gonna be a time

11:37.864 --> 11:39.908
"when I am <i>not </i>on these meds?

11:39.991 --> 11:42.077
I mean, is-is this ever gonna end?"

11:42.160 --> 11:44.871
And... and then he... (laughs)

11:44.954 --> 11:47.457
He says, "One day at time."

11:47.540 --> 11:49.751
One day at a time.

11:49.834 --> 11:53.838
An excellent TV show,
and a terrible answer to my question.

11:53.922 --> 11:57.592
Now, I don't know how it feels

11:57.676 --> 12:00.637
to stare down Alzheimer's.

12:04.140 --> 12:06.101
But I do know how it feels

12:06.184 --> 12:08.395
to look at your life

12:08.478 --> 12:10.897
and to see all the things
that you want from it,

12:10.980 --> 12:14.901
and to have them all seem so unattainable.

12:16.945 --> 12:19.030
Rebecca had a bad day.

12:19.114 --> 12:21.116
She's gonna have more.

12:21.199 --> 12:23.785
You know.

12:23.868 --> 12:28.039
My long-winded advice is for you

12:28.123 --> 12:31.209
to remind her that to you,

12:31.292 --> 12:34.129
her happy future is very real.

12:35.714 --> 12:37.674
One day at a time.

12:41.261 --> 12:43.179
It's a great show.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.223
The reboot is better.

12:45.306 --> 12:47.058
-I know.
-(laughs)

12:47.142 --> 12:49.019
I'm the one who started
the hashtag to get it revived

12:49.102 --> 12:50.770
-after it got canceled.
-Is that right?

12:50.854 --> 12:52.397
You don't cancel Rita Moreno.

12:52.480 --> 12:53.773
-(phone buzzes)
-Amen.

12:53.857 --> 12:55.191
-Yeah.
-(chuckles)

12:55.275 --> 12:56.693
Oh, this is Rebecca's doctor from L.A.

12:56.776 --> 12:58.194
-Yeah, good.
-I got to take this.

12:58.278 --> 13:01.072
Hello. Hi, uh, Dr. Whitaker.

13:01.156 --> 13:02.782
Is that her doctor?
I need to speak with her.

13:02.866 --> 13:04.659
Yeah, yeah. This, uh...
It was this afternoon.

13:04.743 --> 13:06.453
-Give me the...
-It was a very severe episode.

13:06.536 --> 13:08.246
Miguel, I'd like to talk to her.

13:08.329 --> 13:09.789
Randall, just hold on
one second, please. Uh...

13:09.873 --> 13:11.499
Ask her if anything could have

13:11.583 --> 13:13.418
-negatively interacted with her meds.
-Just...

13:13.501 --> 13:15.837
Ask her about the allergy medicine,

13:15.920 --> 13:18.465
the one she took for poison ivy.
Here.

13:20.633 --> 13:22.260
Are you sure she took this?

13:22.344 --> 13:23.678
Yeah, she told me.

13:23.762 --> 13:26.473
Hey, Dr. Whitaker, uh, yeah.

13:26.556 --> 13:29.934
It looks like Rebecca took
an antihistamine with...

13:30.018 --> 13:32.020
Yes, diphenhydramine.

13:33.730 --> 13:36.191
I do remember it from the list.

13:36.274 --> 13:38.109
Okay. Right.

13:38.193 --> 13:40.487
So it could have been a reaction to the...

13:42.530 --> 13:43.990
Thank God. Okay.

13:44.074 --> 13:47.077
Yes, she's resting right now.

13:47.160 --> 13:48.870
Yes.

13:48.953 --> 13:51.039
Absolutely. Um, yes, I will.

13:55.919 --> 13:57.921
♪ ♪

14:25.949 --> 14:27.534
Please forgive me.

14:27.617 --> 14:29.786
I'm so sorry.

14:30.787 --> 14:33.873
She was in...

14:33.957 --> 14:36.167
so much pain.

14:36.251 --> 14:38.336
-(baby crying)
-Shh.

14:38.420 --> 14:40.714
It's okay. Shh.

14:40.797 --> 14:43.842
It's okay.
You've been crying all night.

14:43.925 --> 14:45.969
-Aren't you tired? Huh?
-(crying continues)

14:48.013 --> 14:50.724
-(groans)
-Still bad?

14:50.807 --> 14:51.725
(groans)

14:51.808 --> 14:53.560
We should go to the clinic,

14:53.643 --> 14:55.562
-try to get you looked at.
-No.

14:55.645 --> 14:58.732
If I tell that doctor
I'm on methadone to get clean,

14:58.815 --> 15:00.775
he'll look at me like I'm dirt.
Less than.

15:00.859 --> 15:02.569
-Laurel, please.
-No!

15:02.652 --> 15:04.404
(crying continues)

15:04.487 --> 15:06.698
(Laurel groaning)

15:09.993 --> 15:14.080
I need you to get me
some stuff for the pain.

15:17.667 --> 15:21.046
Please. I've been good.

15:21.129 --> 15:22.797
I have.

15:22.881 --> 15:25.383
LAUREL:
I just-- It hurts so bad.

15:25.467 --> 15:29.137
I just need a little help.
I just need a little help.

15:29.220 --> 15:30.680
Okay? Just one more time.

15:30.764 --> 15:33.141
(baby crying loudly)

15:33.224 --> 15:35.477
So I can be there for the baby.

15:35.560 --> 15:36.770
(William shushing)

15:47.155 --> 15:49.783
♪ ♪

15:51.868 --> 15:54.454
I-I can't do it by myself.

15:58.375 --> 16:00.377
I can't take care of him.

16:04.130 --> 16:06.132
I'm so sorry.

16:07.425 --> 16:09.678
(sobbing)

16:09.761 --> 16:11.846
Please be with him.

16:13.473 --> 16:15.767
Please take care of him.

16:15.850 --> 16:18.311
-(door opens)
-Oh.

16:18.395 --> 16:19.771
(sniffles)

16:24.943 --> 16:26.486
Excuse me.

16:40.667 --> 16:42.669
♪ ♪

16:51.845 --> 16:53.513
He used to pray so hard

16:53.596 --> 16:55.181
you could see the veins in his neck.

16:58.476 --> 16:59.894
<i>Yeah, I remember that.</i>

16:59.978 --> 17:02.522
The veins in his neck.

17:05.066 --> 17:07.318
Never knew what he was asking for.

17:09.029 --> 17:13.116
<i>I used to tell myself</i>
<i>he was asking to be better.</i>

17:14.159 --> 17:16.119
Better to us.

17:16.202 --> 17:17.996
A better man.

17:18.997 --> 17:21.291
<i>And then I would pray.</i>

17:22.542 --> 17:26.087
<i>Pray that it would work.</i>
<i>That he would change.</i>

17:32.052 --> 17:36.514
Then, when he never did...

17:36.598 --> 17:38.892
that's when I gave up on all of this.

17:45.732 --> 17:48.735
Every hand you've dealt me has been crap.

17:48.818 --> 17:50.862
But still, I kept trying.

17:52.655 --> 17:54.616
All these years...

17:56.618 --> 18:00.622
...trying to always do what's right.

18:00.705 --> 18:03.667
Trying to be the better man;
the man that he never was.

18:08.713 --> 18:13.218
Has that made you laugh... seeing me try?

18:14.260 --> 18:18.515
Knowing that, somewhere deep down...

18:18.598 --> 18:21.643
in spite of everything,
that I probably still believed?

18:31.361 --> 18:33.738
The only good thing
that has ever happened to me is her,

18:33.822 --> 18:35.532
and if you--

18:40.620 --> 18:42.622
(sighs)

18:57.637 --> 19:00.682
Please do not take her away from me.

19:04.102 --> 19:05.478
I am begging you.

19:05.562 --> 19:08.857
I'm on my knees begging for her.

19:12.444 --> 19:14.654
Begging for my children.

19:17.157 --> 19:20.160
Take me if you want, just don't...

19:35.467 --> 19:37.427
Just don't.

19:39.763 --> 19:41.765
Don't you dare.

19:49.564 --> 19:52.609
KATE: I had no idea that medications
could interact that way.

19:52.692 --> 19:55.028
-And they're sure it's temporary?
-That's what the doctor said.

19:55.111 --> 19:57.197
Said a reaction like that
can cause an episode

19:57.280 --> 19:59.074
and then it can just wear off.

19:59.157 --> 20:01.284
That was a hell of a catch, Randall.

20:01.368 --> 20:03.244
Back at you.

20:03.328 --> 20:05.997
We're lucky you came, Randall.

20:06.081 --> 20:07.957
-Honestly.
-Yeah.

20:09.000 --> 20:11.252
I'm just happy she's okay.

20:13.713 --> 20:17.050
So, um... I'm gonna take off.

20:17.133 --> 20:18.927
Wait, what? Now?

20:19.010 --> 20:21.346
-But cake.
-I, uh...

20:21.429 --> 20:23.807
I promised Beth and the girls
that I'd get home tonight.

20:23.890 --> 20:26.601
They got a whole thing planned, so...

20:28.645 --> 20:29.854
-Miguel.
-Drive safe.

20:29.938 --> 20:31.481
Tobias.

20:31.564 --> 20:33.483
Sis.

20:34.442 --> 20:36.069
Kev.

20:36.152 --> 20:38.113
Bye, guys.

20:38.196 --> 20:40.615
(door squeaks, shuts)

20:45.704 --> 20:47.038
Hey, Randall.

20:48.957 --> 20:51.418
So, I was, uh... I was hoping

20:51.501 --> 20:53.920
that you and Kev would talk, you know?

20:54.004 --> 20:56.089
-Clear the air.
-Kate...

20:57.507 --> 20:59.592
I'm not taking any sides.

20:59.676 --> 21:01.011
I know I live in L.A. with him,

21:01.094 --> 21:03.805
but I am totally Switzerland on this one.

21:03.888 --> 21:06.141
Okay.

21:07.183 --> 21:09.185
-Randall.
-Hmm?

21:09.269 --> 21:10.562
Are we good?

21:11.604 --> 21:14.149
I mean, I've been texting
and reaching out,

21:14.232 --> 21:16.609
and I haven't heard
anything back, really, and...

21:16.693 --> 21:18.611
I'm just so worried about...

21:18.695 --> 21:21.197
about you and Beth and the girls.

21:21.281 --> 21:24.242
You know, with everything
that's going on in the news.

21:24.325 --> 21:26.036
I'm so overwhelmed by it,
I can't even imagine

21:26.119 --> 21:29.289
what you guys are all going through, so..

21:30.749 --> 21:32.167
I'm so sorry.

21:37.213 --> 21:38.715
Sorry about what?

21:41.009 --> 21:44.471
Specifically,
what are you apologizing for?

21:46.556 --> 21:50.226
I'm just-- I'm... sorry about
what's going on in the country

21:50.310 --> 21:53.021
-and the protests and...
-Okay.

21:53.104 --> 21:55.565
But you've never apologized before.

21:55.648 --> 21:57.692
And this isn't the first Black person

21:57.776 --> 21:59.694
to be killed on camera.

22:01.696 --> 22:05.283
No, it's... it's not.

22:09.621 --> 22:10.955
I don't know, this feels different.

22:11.039 --> 22:13.667
Not for me, Kate.

22:13.750 --> 22:16.711
I-It's never been different for me.

22:18.755 --> 22:20.507
We grew up in the same house.

22:20.590 --> 22:22.592
Things like this have been
happening to Black people

22:22.676 --> 22:25.679
for years, and we've never
talked about it.

22:25.762 --> 22:27.555
Not once.

22:27.639 --> 22:32.352
Not once in 40 years.

22:32.435 --> 22:33.645
I...

22:35.563 --> 22:37.816
I don't know what to say.
I don't want to say--

22:37.899 --> 22:40.527
-I don't want to say the wrong thing.
-Okay.

22:40.610 --> 22:43.530
So, growing up, I, uh, I just had to keep

22:43.613 --> 22:47.492
so many things to myself because...

22:47.575 --> 22:51.037
I didn't want to make you guys feel bad.

22:51.121 --> 22:52.706
I didn't want you to have to worry about

22:52.789 --> 22:55.250
saying the wrong thing.

22:56.584 --> 22:58.253
Oh, God...

23:00.505 --> 23:03.216
Well, you're right.
I mean, we never talked about it

23:03.299 --> 23:06.094
as kids, and I think Mom and Dad
did the best they could,

23:06.177 --> 23:08.596
I guess, but...

23:08.680 --> 23:10.432
but I didn't get involved,
I-I didn't even...

23:10.515 --> 23:12.517
See, I hate this, Kate.

23:14.060 --> 23:16.312
I hate seeing you upset.

23:16.396 --> 23:19.065
And normally I would hug you,

23:19.149 --> 23:22.527
and I would tell you that
you did all the right things.

23:22.610 --> 23:25.238
I would try to make it all okay for you.

23:25.321 --> 23:26.906
But if I did that, Kate...

23:26.990 --> 23:30.660
If I made things better for you,
then where does that leave me?

23:33.830 --> 23:35.957
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

23:36.041 --> 23:40.295
That has been my pattern all my life.

23:40.378 --> 23:43.340
And honestly, Kate, it is exhausting.

23:46.468 --> 23:48.261
I'm exhausted.

23:50.305 --> 23:53.391
And all I want to do right now
is go home and be with my wife

23:53.475 --> 23:56.186
and my girls.

23:59.064 --> 24:00.231
Okay.

24:00.315 --> 24:02.734
Okay, um...

24:05.445 --> 24:06.613
I love you.

24:06.696 --> 24:08.615
I love you, too.

24:12.035 --> 24:13.828
Happy birthday, Sis.

24:13.912 --> 24:16.039
Happy birthday.

24:31.638 --> 24:33.640
♪ ♪

24:52.701 --> 24:54.911
(phone line trilling)

24:54.994 --> 24:57.247
<i>STANLEY (over phone):</i>
<i>Yeah?</i>

24:57.330 --> 24:59.708
It's Jack.

25:04.504 --> 25:06.423
Been a while.

25:09.217 --> 25:10.552
Yeah.

25:13.096 --> 25:14.180
<i>You okay?</i>

25:14.264 --> 25:16.266
Yeah. I...

25:19.436 --> 25:21.146
No, I...

25:22.605 --> 25:23.648
I don't know.

25:26.359 --> 25:28.945
<i>Can I ask you something?</i>

25:33.241 --> 25:36.369
What were you praying for?
I mean, you know,

25:36.453 --> 25:38.413
back when we used to go to church.

25:41.666 --> 25:43.376
<i>You need money again or something?</i>

25:43.460 --> 25:45.795
<i>Wh-What's going on?</i>

25:45.879 --> 25:47.255
No, I'm good.

25:49.632 --> 25:52.594
I don't know why I called.
I was just... having a day.

25:52.677 --> 25:54.679
Uh... I'll let you go.

25:54.763 --> 25:56.806
-I-I hope you're okay.
<i>-Jack.</i>

25:58.850 --> 26:00.018
<i>Yeah?</i>

26:02.645 --> 26:06.483
<i>Uh, I prayed my kids</i>
<i>would turn out better than I did.</i>

26:12.489 --> 26:14.282
I'm trying, Pop.

26:15.950 --> 26:17.285
I'm really trying.

26:17.369 --> 26:19.412
Yeah, I-I know.

26:21.998 --> 26:24.918
-I gotta go.
<i>-Hey, Jackie?</i>

26:26.961 --> 26:28.296
Yeah?

26:29.881 --> 26:32.133
Happy birthday, kid.

26:32.217 --> 26:35.303
♪ <i>I been down this road before </i>♪

26:35.387 --> 26:37.222
♪ <i>I remember every tree... </i>♪

26:37.305 --> 26:38.515
Thanks, Pop.

26:40.392 --> 26:42.519
♪ <i>Every single blade of grass </i>♪

26:42.602 --> 26:45.855
♪ <i>Holds a special place for me </i>♪

26:47.732 --> 26:51.528
♪ <i>And I remember every town </i>♪

26:51.611 --> 26:54.155
♪ <i>And every hotel room </i>♪

26:56.157 --> 26:58.576
♪ <i>Every song I ever sang </i>♪

26:58.660 --> 27:01.246
♪ <i>On a guitar out of tune </i>♪

27:02.872 --> 27:06.751
♪ <i>I remember everything </i>♪

27:06.835 --> 27:09.462
♪ <i>Things I can't forget </i>♪

27:10.714 --> 27:14.426
♪ <i>The way you turned and smiled on me... </i>♪

27:14.509 --> 27:17.429
And he wound up here.

27:17.512 --> 27:21.057
Exact same place, exact same day.

27:21.141 --> 27:24.853
♪ <i>Your ocean eyes of blue... </i>♪

27:24.936 --> 27:26.688
Just look at him, Bec.

27:26.771 --> 27:28.857
<i>Placed right there.</i>

27:28.940 --> 27:30.525
<i>Right next to ours.</i>

27:30.608 --> 27:32.235
♪ <i>Like roses miss the dew. </i>♪

27:32.318 --> 27:33.486
KEVIN:
Hey, Randall.

27:35.071 --> 27:36.906
Hey, listen, I just wanted to, uh...

27:36.990 --> 27:40.201
Just wanted to say thanks for, uh...

27:40.285 --> 27:41.536
thanks for coming out, you know,

27:41.619 --> 27:42.954
I really appreciate it.
If you hadn't, we, uh...

27:43.038 --> 27:45.165
No. Yeah, of course.

27:45.248 --> 27:47.625
(mutters indistinctly)

27:49.127 --> 27:50.337
Yeah.

27:50.420 --> 27:53.381
-I should go to beat the traffic.
-Yeah.

27:53.465 --> 27:55.884
Hey, Randall, uh...

27:57.260 --> 27:59.346
I'm having a-a girl.

27:59.429 --> 28:02.515
A girl and a boy.
We just found out.

28:08.229 --> 28:09.814
Congratulations, Kev.
That's great news.

28:09.898 --> 28:12.233
Thanks.

28:12.317 --> 28:15.028
Yeah, you're the first person I've told.
(chuckles)

28:18.698 --> 28:20.116
And I feel like,
I don't know, I feel like the boy,

28:20.200 --> 28:22.202
you know, I was a boy once,
I can handle a boy, right?

28:22.285 --> 28:25.121
But the girl, I...

28:25.205 --> 28:27.749
Ooh! So...

28:29.834 --> 28:32.379
Anyway, you got any advice for me?

28:35.882 --> 28:38.343
You'll let her get away with anything.

28:40.720 --> 28:43.473
But her mom will be there
to fix your mistakes.

28:43.556 --> 28:46.434
Mom will probably be better
at everything, honestly.

28:46.518 --> 28:49.688
Yeah.

28:49.771 --> 28:52.649
Yeah, she probably will be.

28:55.443 --> 28:57.779
You know, in the strangest of ways...

28:59.823 --> 29:02.242
I feel like I might have...

29:02.325 --> 29:05.912
really found someone
really special, you know?

29:15.630 --> 29:17.215
I gotta go.

29:18.258 --> 29:19.342
Yeah.

29:19.426 --> 29:21.845
Happy birthday.

29:23.430 --> 29:25.098
Happy birthday, Randall.

29:32.147 --> 29:34.733
(engine starts)

29:34.816 --> 29:37.986
(car drives away)

29:43.366 --> 29:45.368
♪ ♪

29:56.379 --> 29:58.006
<i>You gonna keep staring at me,</i>

29:58.089 --> 29:59.799
or you gonna tell me your name?

29:59.883 --> 30:01.593
WILLIAM:
(chuckles) I don't know.

30:01.676 --> 30:04.346
You gonna tell me your name?

30:06.431 --> 30:08.641
-I'm Laurel.
-William.

30:08.725 --> 30:10.685
But around here they call me...

30:10.769 --> 30:12.645
BUS DRIVER:
Hey, Shakespeare!

30:12.729 --> 30:14.814
Shakespeare, it's your stop.
You're home, kid.

30:14.898 --> 30:16.608
You getting off or what?

30:16.691 --> 30:21.321
No, I'm not getting off.
So just... keep going.

30:27.744 --> 30:30.205
♪ ♪

30:36.586 --> 30:39.047
(sighs)

30:43.385 --> 30:45.553
(phone buzzing)

30:50.058 --> 30:51.059
Hi, Randall.

30:51.142 --> 30:55.271
Hi, Dr. Leigh.
Uh, sorry to bother you.

30:55.355 --> 30:57.774
I hope it's an okay time to...

30:59.359 --> 31:01.861
No, of course.
I-I-I saw your name,

31:01.945 --> 31:04.447
and I wanted to make sure
everything was all right.

31:06.032 --> 31:09.661
Yeah, no, everything's all right.

31:09.744 --> 31:11.705
But...

31:14.165 --> 31:15.875
When we first met, Dr. Leigh,

31:15.959 --> 31:18.712
you made a point of pointing out

31:18.795 --> 31:21.840
just how few Black men
seek you out for therapy.

31:21.923 --> 31:25.844
It's a "very small number,"
were your words.

31:25.927 --> 31:28.096
<i>(chuckles)</i>
<i>I remember.</i>

31:28.179 --> 31:30.724
I made a conscious choice to start seeing

31:30.807 --> 31:32.851
a white female therapist.

31:34.185 --> 31:35.937
I know that.

31:36.021 --> 31:37.522
It's complicated for me,

31:37.605 --> 31:39.232
and I can't claim to understand it,

31:39.315 --> 31:41.359
but I-- I do know it.

31:41.443 --> 31:43.862
If that makes sense.

31:48.033 --> 31:52.037
There are things, Dr. Leigh,
that I don't feel comfortable

31:52.120 --> 31:54.164
talking to you about.

31:55.498 --> 32:00.587
There's stuff I-I put away
when I enter your office, and...

32:00.670 --> 32:02.964
that doesn't help me get better.

32:04.466 --> 32:06.468
And there's nothing you can do
to make me more comfortable.

32:06.551 --> 32:09.471
I just... (chuckles)

32:09.554 --> 32:11.765
I need something different.

32:16.227 --> 32:21.066
I'm gonna make a change
and find a Black therapist.

32:21.149 --> 32:25.028
And I just wanted
to tell you that directly.

32:27.447 --> 32:31.284
<i>Randall, obviously your mental</i>
<i>health is what's important here,</i>

32:31.368 --> 32:33.953
<i>and if that's something that</i>
<i>you're feeling strongly about,</i>

32:34.037 --> 32:36.414
<i>I completely respect that decision.</i>

32:40.710 --> 32:42.420
Hey.

32:42.504 --> 32:46.132
I knew that the meal
was important to you, so...

32:47.884 --> 32:49.636
I'm doing the best that I can.

32:49.719 --> 32:52.639
So be gentle in your critique.

33:01.356 --> 33:05.568
Is that what it's gonna feel like...

33:05.652 --> 33:07.445
when I eventually...

33:07.529 --> 33:09.322
We don't have to worry about that.

33:09.406 --> 33:11.825
Not-not today.

33:17.288 --> 33:20.875
-You know what's so strange?
-Hmm?

33:20.959 --> 33:24.295
I'm not worried about
forgetting about the big stuff.

33:28.049 --> 33:30.260
It's the little things.

33:30.343 --> 33:32.345
It's the...

33:33.346 --> 33:36.391
It's the regular...

33:36.474 --> 33:39.394
Saturday when the kids were little.

33:39.477 --> 33:42.897
(no audio)

33:42.981 --> 33:46.192
A day when nothing big really happens.
J...

33:46.276 --> 33:48.862
(laughs):
We were just there, a normal family,

33:48.945 --> 33:51.406
like any other normal family.

33:51.489 --> 33:55.702
Laughing and talking and...

33:55.785 --> 33:57.495
(no audio)

33:57.579 --> 34:00.707
...playing pin the tail on the donkey.

34:06.838 --> 34:10.008
That's the stuff I'm not ready
to let go of yet.

34:12.594 --> 34:14.596
I want to show you something.

34:16.431 --> 34:17.349
Come on.

34:17.432 --> 34:19.476
-Come on.
-What...

34:28.985 --> 34:31.071
-I chopped down the dead tree.
-Yeah.

34:31.154 --> 34:34.157
And I know that you said
you wanted to plant a sapling...

34:34.240 --> 34:36.618
-Mm-hmm. -...so that we could
get fruit sooner, but,

34:36.701 --> 34:40.789
I don't know, it just seemed, um...
too easy.

34:40.872 --> 34:44.751
So, instead, I got these.

34:44.834 --> 34:46.753
Oh...

34:47.921 --> 34:51.549
Now, these should bear fruit

34:51.633 --> 34:55.011
in about... six to ten years.

34:57.222 --> 34:59.140
Six to ten years?
I don't...

34:59.224 --> 35:00.850
I am not in a rush.

35:00.934 --> 35:03.520
One day at a time.

35:03.603 --> 35:06.439
And then another...

35:06.523 --> 35:08.483
And then another.

35:09.776 --> 35:11.486
I love you.

35:11.569 --> 35:14.280
-I love you.
-Thank you.

35:17.992 --> 35:19.953
Hey.

35:21.329 --> 35:23.081
Guess what.

35:26.126 --> 35:28.128
What's going on?

35:31.423 --> 35:33.800
I can't stop thinking about
what Randall said.

35:36.469 --> 35:38.388
I've been so oblivious.

35:39.848 --> 35:41.766
(sighs)

35:41.850 --> 35:44.477
-What can I do?
-Noth-Nothing.

35:44.561 --> 35:47.063
That's sweet, but I'm gonna have to

35:47.147 --> 35:49.065
sit with these feelings a while.

35:51.693 --> 35:55.030
Well, we'll get it all right
raising our children.

35:56.322 --> 35:58.241
Yeah. Yes.

35:58.324 --> 36:01.202
Raising our children,

36:01.286 --> 36:04.748
-which is the plural of "child."
-Mm-hmm.

36:04.831 --> 36:06.958
Children.

36:07.042 --> 36:08.793
Are you doing something confusing?

36:08.877 --> 36:10.295
'Cause I don't-- I don't get it.

36:10.378 --> 36:12.005
Apparently. Listen.

36:12.088 --> 36:14.924
I just got six messages
from the adoption agency.

36:15.008 --> 36:18.595
Kate, we have a match.

36:18.678 --> 36:20.930
-(humming)
-Wh...

36:21.014 --> 36:23.016
What?

36:23.099 --> 36:24.684
They found us a match.

36:24.768 --> 36:27.395
-For real?
-Yes.

36:27.479 --> 36:31.191
-We're getting a baby?
-We gettin' a ba...

36:31.274 --> 36:33.568
♪ ♪

36:46.122 --> 36:49.584
♪ <i>I don't think you want grand gestures </i>♪

36:49.668 --> 36:53.505
♪ <i>Just a simple, faithful friend </i>♪

36:53.588 --> 36:56.883
♪ <i>Someone who will walk it with you </i>♪

36:56.966 --> 37:00.470
♪ <i>All the way to the end </i>♪

37:00.553 --> 37:04.349
♪ <i>Someone who can live and love you </i>♪

37:04.432 --> 37:07.394
♪ <i>Singing how I've come to know </i>♪

37:07.477 --> 37:09.312
♪ <i>Oh, oh, oh </i>♪

37:09.396 --> 37:11.314
♪ <i>Oh, oh </i>♪

37:13.316 --> 37:17.153
♪ <i>You're like the sun that gives </i>♪

37:17.237 --> 37:19.322
♪ <i>The moon its glow </i>♪

37:19.406 --> 37:22.325
♪ <i>Oh, oh </i>♪

37:22.409 --> 37:26.246
♪ <i>You're my, oh, you are my </i>♪

37:26.329 --> 37:30.125
♪ <i>My sweet refuge </i>♪

37:30.208 --> 37:31.334
♪ <i>You're my... </i>♪

37:31.418 --> 37:33.169
BETH:
And another one.

37:33.253 --> 37:34.838
(laughs softly)

37:35.839 --> 37:38.216
Mmm.

37:40.010 --> 37:41.928
(indistinct chatter)

37:42.012 --> 37:45.098
♪ <i>But we'll leave them chasing tails </i>♪

37:45.181 --> 37:47.559
♪ <i>'Cause you're my, oh, you are my... </i>♪

37:47.642 --> 37:50.437
I'm not having a breakdown,
Beth. I'm really not.

37:52.439 --> 37:55.900
I'm healthier than I've been in years.

37:58.319 --> 38:01.531
But what I'm dealing with at work,

38:01.614 --> 38:03.950
and what we're dealing with as a people,

38:04.034 --> 38:06.453
day after day...

38:09.122 --> 38:12.042
-It's just so tragic, Beth.
-Mm-hmm.

38:13.668 --> 38:16.504
So much loss.

38:20.216 --> 38:22.886
It's just so sad.

38:25.972 --> 38:29.809
I-I'm not falling apart.
I'm not having a breakdown.

38:32.312 --> 38:35.899
I'm just really, really sad, baby.

38:39.819 --> 38:41.654
(exhales)

38:41.738 --> 38:45.075
When my dad was dying, I...

38:45.158 --> 38:48.078
remember he said that it's the tragedies

38:48.161 --> 38:50.413
that define our lives.

38:52.415 --> 38:53.958
"They are the fence posts on which

38:54.042 --> 38:56.836
the rest of our lives hang, baby girl."

38:59.172 --> 39:01.716
I always think about that.

39:01.800 --> 39:03.927
Like...

39:04.010 --> 39:07.847
our lives just hanging there,

39:07.931 --> 39:11.142
between these really sad fence posts.

39:17.232 --> 39:19.567
Baby.

39:19.651 --> 39:21.277
You were born out of tragedy.

39:21.361 --> 39:24.364
♪ <i>I need you, I need you... </i>♪

39:24.447 --> 39:27.200
<i>Multiple tragedies.</i>

39:27.283 --> 39:31.079
♪ <i>Lord, every day, I need you... </i>♪

39:31.162 --> 39:33.665
<i>All that loss, all that sadness.</i>

39:33.748 --> 39:37.711
♪ <i>I need you, I need you... </i>♪

39:37.794 --> 39:40.630
And look what you've hung
on your fence posts.

39:42.257 --> 39:44.175
Look right in front of you.

39:44.259 --> 39:46.219
Right here in this room, and...

39:46.302 --> 39:47.554
♪ <i>You are mine... </i>♪

39:47.637 --> 39:49.848
I mean, look what you did
with all of that.

39:49.931 --> 39:51.933
(soft laughter)

39:54.686 --> 39:57.230
Do you see it?

39:57.313 --> 39:59.149
I see it.

40:00.150 --> 40:04.779
You are a beautiful, resilient man.

40:06.031 --> 40:09.200
The world is a brilliant, resilient place.

40:11.202 --> 40:13.663
We fight on.

40:15.582 --> 40:17.792
